import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['delay'] = pd.to_datetime(data['delay'], format='%H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')
    plt.hist(data['delay'].dt.total_seconds() / 60, bins=range(0, 601, 30), color='blue', edgecolor='black')
    plt.axvline(data['delay'].dt.total_seconds().median() / 60, color='red', label='Median delay: {:.2f}'.format(data['delay'].dt.total_seconds().median() / 60))
    plt.xlabel('Delay (minutes)')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight delays?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['distance'] = pd.to_numeric(data['distance'], errors='coerce')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.boxplot(data['distance'], vert=False)
    ax.set_xlabel('Distance')
    ax.axvline(data['distance'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Mean: {data["distance"].mean():0.2f}')
    ax.legend()
    plt.title('What is the average distance of flights?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['count'] = 1
    df = data.groupby(['origin', 'destination']).count().reset_index()
    df = df.sort_values(by='count', ascending=False).head(10)
    plt.bar(df['origin'] + ' to ' + df['destination'], df['count'])
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.title('Which origin and destination airports have the highest number of flights?')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data.sort_values(by='date')
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['delay'])
    plt.title('What is the trend of flight delays over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Delay')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

    plt.xlabel('Distance')
